items.preText: 6.44pm We're back, and Liton Das and Imrul Kayes are in the middle. Jarvis will open the bowling. 6.30pm We thought before this game that it might be too early in the winter for dew to be an issue under lights, but it seems there is a little moisture on the outfield. That will make things a little more difficult for Zimbabwe's spinners, and what's more it might just quicken the track up a little bit. 6.27pm Hello everyone, Liam Brickhill here, making a wildcard return to online text-based cricket commentary. Zimbabwe looked set for 290 when Brendan Taylor and Sean Williams were building their 77-run third wicket stand, but their innings lost steam in the second half and Bangladesh did superbly well at the death. "Quite good death bowling from Bangladesh," Seth points out. "Only 19 runs and three wickets in the last five overs." Agreed, though as Alistair Campbell just pointed out on telly before he nipped off for his mid-match dinner, it's hard to judge a pitch until both teams have batted on it. And this didn't seem a track for free-flowing strokeplay once the ball got a little older.
items.text: Jarvis hit's a length on middle and off to start, Liton Das tapping to midwicket. He wants a single, but there's nothing there.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

items.text: a little wider this time from Jarvis, but Das can't find the timing he's looking for on a backfoot punch.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

items.text: stinger! This one leapt off a length, zipping off the surface and beating the outside edge. It dipped a little on the way through to Taylor, and he's left wringing his hand in pain no major damage though.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

items.text: this one hits a wobbling seam and thuds into Liton's front pad. There's a huge appeal from both sides of the wicket, and Umpire Rod Tucker raises the finger ... The batsman's not convinced though, and calls for a review. And that's a good call! The ball actually seamed a little too far towards leg, and the ball tracker shows it would have missed leg stump.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

items.text: first runs off the bat, and they come via a neat little punch through the off side. In front of square, but to the left of extra cover, and they scamper back for the second.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Liton Das, 2 runs

items.text: fuller and straighter from the Zimbabwean quick, and it's met with the full face of the bat. The ball rolls to mid-off.
items.postText: An eventful first over there. Zimbabwe thought they had their man.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

items.preText: Here's Chatara to share the new ball duties. He's got a slip in place, and another catcher close it at extra cover. A hint that there's a touch of slowness to this track?
items.text: he's just too straight to start, and Kayes opens his scorebook with a nudge through leg.
items.shortText: Chatara to Imrul Kayes, 1 run

items.text: has this kept a little low? Das was camped on the back foot and waited on a pull, but the ball just died on him a little and his shot dribbles to midwicket.
items.shortText: Chatara to Liton Das, no run

items.text: cracking delivery! Chatara goes wide on the crease to deliver an outswinger on a good length, and Das is caught a little flat-footed as he gropes outside off.
items.shortText: Chatara to Liton Das, no run

items.text: not much foot movement here either, but he's laced this through cover point. Right on top of it, eyes over the ball, and a lightning quick outfield does the rest.
items.shortText: Chatara to Liton Das, FOUR runs

items.text: on the leg side this time! Chatara over-corrects, shooting one down at his pads and Das sends it on its way to the square leg boundary with a flick of the wrists.
items.shortText: Chatara to Liton Das, FOUR runs

items.text: Chatara finds a better line outside off with another outswinger, but Das won't be tempted into a shot.
items.shortText: Chatara to Liton Das, no run

items.text: edged, but it drops short of second slip! This one from Jarvis went like an offcutter, and Kayes thrust his hands out at the ball even as it left him. Moor tumbles to his right at second slip, but the ball drops well in front of him,
items.shortText: Jarvis to Imrul Kayes, no run

items.text: a touch straighter, and this time Kayes moves a little more fluently into position to push to mid-off
items.shortText: Jarvis to Imrul Kayes, no run

items.text: Jarvis belts out an appeal after a length delivery pings off Kayes' front pad, and when it's turned down they consider a review ... there's nothing going though, and Masakadza says no. He's right, too - it pitched well outside leg.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Imrul Kayes, no run

items.preText: Elton Chigumbura is at mid on and he offers Jarvis a little sage advice before he delivers the next ball. At the other end, Moor has some running repairs done to the hand he stopped that edge at second slip with.
items.text: on a length, and Kayes presses his weight forward to push defensively at the ball.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Imrul Kayes, no run

items.text: a length delivery rises off a leg stump line, and Kayes rides the bounce to pick up a single to fine leg.
items.postText: The dew I mentioned before the chase began seems to be getting a little more serious. Several Zimbabwean fielders have flannels stuck into the back of their trousers to dry the ball between deliveries.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Imrul Kayes, 1 run

items.text: Jarvis finds a tight line on off stump, and Das offers an equally tight backfoot defence.
items.shortText: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

items.text: Kayes looks suspiciously at the track after this one grips the surface and cuts across him to find the leading edge of the bat. The ball trickles safely into the off side
items.shortText: Chatara to Imrul Kayes, no run

items.text: Chatara's line has been a little erratic, and he fires this well down the leg side. Good take from a tumbling Taylor
items.shortText: Chatara to Imrul Kayes, 1 wide

items.text: a booming drive, but Kayes loses his shape in the shot and it ends up as a bottom-handed toe-end to mid on.
items.shortText: Chatara to Imrul Kayes, no run

items.text: flicked off the hip, and an easy single is the result.
items.postText: They're doing the Chattogram Wave up in the stands. There's a very vocal crowd in tonight.
items.shortText: Chatara to Imrul Kayes, 1 run

items.text: sublime! Das just leaned over this leg-stump half volley, and once it had the beating of mid-on the fielder could never catch up. Chigumbura puts in a dive, but succeeds only in tumbling into the rope himself.
items.shortText: Chatara to Liton Das, FOUR runs

items.text: Chatara is a little straight once again, but this time he pings the leg-side field.
items.shortText: Chatara to Liton Das, no run

items.text: that's a little sloppy from PJ Moor. Das flicks one almost straight to him at midwicket, but he over-runs it and allows a single. Is he struggling with that hand still?
